subSubSection.paragraph:
Genocidaris maculata Agassiz, 1869
— Mortensen 1903: 85 , 1927a: 292 , 1943b: 358–362 , figs. 219, 220, pl. 18, figs. 37– 47; $ Koehler 1909: 226–227 , pl. 31, fig. 3; Koehler 1921b: 115–116 , fig. 76; $ H.L. Clark 1925: 76–77 ; Tortonese 1965: 321– 322 , fig. 150; Serafy & Fell 1985: 21 ; Pereira 1997: 334 ;
García-Diez et al . 2005: 50
; Mironov 2006: 211–212 ;
Micael & Costa 2010: 323
;
Micael et al . 2012: 4
;

See: Agassiz (1869: 262–263) ; Mortensen (1943b) ; Mironov (2006) ;
Benavides-Serrato et al . (2012: 70)
.

Occurrence:
Mediterranean Sea and Atlantic (Tortonesen 1965); in the West from Cape Cod, through the Caribbean to North 
Brazil
waters (
Serafy & Fell 1985
); in the East from the North African coasts to the Gulf of 
Guinea
(
Cadenat 1938
), including the Azores (Koehler 1990), Madeira (
Jesus & Abreu 1998
), Canary archipelagos (
Mortensen 1943b
), and Gorringe, Josephine and Seine seamounts (
Mironov 2006
).

Habitat:
sandy to coralligenous substrates (
Koehler 1909
, 
1921b
); feeds on bottom material, ingesting small benthic animals (
e.g.,
foraminiferans, molluscs and bryozoans; 
Serafy & Fell 1985
).
